BT 1 0 0 1 0 135 Tm /F1 9 Tf 12 TL -0.095167 Tw (General anesthesia has been used since 1846. No one knows how it works. Chemically unrelated molecules -- noble gases,) Tj T* 0 Tw (ethers, alkanes, phenols, neurosteroids -- all abolish consciousness at concentrations predicted by their lipid solubility \(the) Tj T* (Meyer-Overton correlation, 1899\). The dose-response is unnaturally sharp \(Hill coefficient ~20\). The effect is perfectly) Tj T* (reversible. We show that general anesthesia is not a pharmacological phenomenon but a phase transition: the anesthetic) Tj T* (increases the effective decoherence rate gamma_eff above the critical threshold gamma_c, collapsing the brain's coherent) Tj T* (state. The Meyer-Overton correlation falls out because lipid solubility determines how effectively the agent disrupts the) Tj T* (Debye shielding at membrane interfaces. The Hill coefficient of ~20 is a phase transition, not cooperativity. MAC \(minimum) Tj T* (alveolar concentration\) IS gamma_c -- a physical constant, not a pharmacological variable. Noble gas anesthesia requires) Tj T* (no chemistry because London dispersion forces alone can disrupt the coherence channel. The xenon isotope experiment) Tj T* -0.10995 Tw (\(Li, Turin et al., 2018 -- 129-Xe with spin-1/2 is more potent than 132-Xe with spin-0, despite identical chemistry\) is predicted) Tj T* 0 Tw (by the framework: nuclear spin provides an additional decoherence channel. Recovery from anesthesia is the detuned) Tj T* (recovery phenomenon observed on IBM quantum hardware \(Paper 26C\). Six testable predictions are stated.) Tj T* ET
